# BiomeJS Code Style Rules

BiomeJS (`@biomejs/biome`) is the sole linting and formatting tool for this project (see [ADR-004](../architecture/adr/ADR-004-biome-linting-formatting.md)). ESLint and Prettier are not used and must not be added.

The authoritative configuration is the root [`biome.json`](../../biome.json). All rules below are derived from it.

---

## Formatting

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Indent style | Spaces |
| Indent width | 4 |
| Line ending | LF |
| Line width | 120 characters |
| Quote style | Single quotes `'` |
| Semicolons | Always |
| Trailing commas | ES5 (objects, arrays, parameters) |
| Arrow function parentheses | Omit when single parameter (`x => x`) |

**Generated code must comply with these settings.** Do not use double quotes, tabs, or omit semicolons.

---

## Linting Rules

### Style

- **`useConst`** (`error`): Always use `const` for variables that are never reassigned. Use `let` only when reassignment is necessary.

```ts
// ✅
const result = compute();

// ❌
let result = compute();
```

- **`useBlockStatements`** (`error`): Always wrap `if`, `else`, `for`, `while`, `do` bodies in curly braces, even for single-line bodies.

```ts
// ✅
if (condition) {
    doSomething();
}

// ❌
if (condition) doSomething();
```

### Suspicious

- **`noDoubleEquals`** (`error`): Use strict equality `===` and `!==`. Never use `==` or `!=`.

```ts
// ✅
if (value === null) { ... }

// ❌
if (value == null) { ... }
```

- **`noVar`** (`error`): Never use `var`. Use `const` or `let`.

```ts
// ✅
const x = 1;

// ❌
var x = 1;
```

- **`noConsole`** (`off`): Console usage is allowed globally. It can be restricted per file pattern via `biome.json` overrides.

---

## Commands

Run from the workspace root:

```bash
# Lint and auto-fix
pnpm lint

# Format and auto-fix
pnpm format

# Lint + format in one pass (recommended before commit)
pnpm check
```

---

## Configuration Constraints

- Do **not** create per-package `biome.json` files unless a specific package requires a narrow override (e.g. relaxing a rule for generated files). All overrides must be in the root `biome.json` under the `overrides` array.
- Do **not** add `.eslintrc`, `.prettierrc`, or any ESLint/Prettier configuration anywhere in the monorepo.
- Test files (`*.spec.ts`, `*.test.ts`) and demo files (`*.demo.ts`) have dedicated overrides in `biome.json` and must not be formatted differently by hand.
